<p>Aerial photo taken on Oct. 21, 2020 shows the auntumn scenery of Huanglong Mountain Scenic Area, Huanglong County, Yan'an City, northwest China's Shaanxi Province. Huanglong County covers an area of 2752 square kilometers, governs 5 towns and 2 townships, and has a total population of 50,000, including 11 ethnic groups from 24 provinces and autonomous regions across the country. The average altitude is 1100 meters, the average annual precipitation is 563.9 mm, and the frost-free period averages 190 days. It is a national ecological function area, a provincial secondary natural forest reserve, and one of the country’s eight major shelter forests. (Huang Long/Guangming Picture)</p>
